snippet.title: Chocolate Nut Bread
snippet.description: Chocolate Nut Bread dessert loaves are a cinch to make -- keep some on hand for snack attacks or unexpected guests.

snippet.title: Mini Chip Snowball Cookies
snippet.description: These Mini Chip Snowball Cookies will add an attractive contrast to any holiday or special occasion cookie selection with their round shape and powdered sugar coating.

snippet.title: Chunky Chocolate Chip Peanut Butter Cookies
snippet.description: These tasty Chunky Chocolate Chip Peanut Butter Cookies are easy to make and easily will delight your friends and family.

snippet.title: Pumpkin Cranberry Cookies
snippet.description: These jazzed up Pumpkin Cranberry Cookies have extra pizazz-- your family will love them!

snippet.title: Molten Chocolate Cakes
snippet.description: Enjoy these delicious molten cakes with a deep, rich chocolate center. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or add a dollop of whipped cream or ice cream for a truly elegant dessert.

snippet.title: Butterscotch Gingerbread Cookies
snippet.description: Butterscotch morsels add their sweet creaminess to this classic gingerbread cookie. The ultimate treat, warm from the oven with a glass of cold milk.

snippet.title: Peanut Butter Pie with Chocolate-Covered Pretzel Crust
snippet.description: The Peanut Butter Pie with Chocolate-Covered Pretzel Crust was created by blogger, Amanda Brown. To learn more about Amanda, visit her blog at Amanda Jane Brown .

snippet.title: Homemade Pie Crust Recipe
snippet.description: Homemade Pie Crust Recipe is a no-fail recipe made easily with ingredients usually found in most kitchens. Be sure to use cold water and keep well-wrapped until ready to use.

snippet.title: Sensibly Delicious Pumpkin Cranberry Bread
snippet.description: Sensibly Delicious Pumpkin Cranberry Bread is an ideal treat for breakfast, lunch or any time. This easy-to-make recipe is perfect for you to try all year round.

snippet.title: Swedish Meatballs with Noodles
snippet.description: Meatballs and ribbon noodles are a quintessential Swedish dish. Moistened with evaporated milk and seasoned with dill, these tender and aromatic meatballs are the perfect partner for luscious noodles and gravy. This is great for both family gatherings or casual entertaining.
